 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of the pieces of work necessary to complete a project.</p> 

   <p>This module is constructed from several ISO/TS Application 
   modules.  The Work_structure_arm contains the information necessary to 
   defined the work to be performed. </p>
      
   <p>The Work_structure_arm provides for the identification and 
     characterization of a <module_ref linkend="work_request:introduction"/> 
     and a <module_ref linkend="work_order:introduction"/>. It provides 
     for an association to be made between the work request and the 
     <module_ref linkend="observation:introduction"/> which initiated 
     the work request. It contains an identification of the activities 
     governed by a work order. It defines the hierarchy of tasks to be 
     performed along with required inputs, and deliverable products 
     and information.  It contains the definition and quantification 
     of planned as well as completed 
     <module_ref linkend="work_output:introduction"/>.</p> 

   <p>Hyperlink to Annex <module_ref linkend="Work_structure:f_usage_guide">F</module_ref>  
  for AP233 concept model introductory material associated with work structure capabilities 
  enabled within AP233 and its connectivity to modules used.</p> 

   </purpose>

 <!-- Items in scope -->
 <inscope>
   <li>identification and characterization a work request and work order;</li>
   <li>association of a work request with an activity method;</li>
   <li>identification of the product or activity data affected by the work request;</li>
   <li>identification of the activities that are governed by a work order;</li>
   <li>the definition and quantification of planned as well as recorded work outputs;</li>
   <li>the relationships between the work output and detailed descriptions of the output.</li>
 </inscope>

 <!-- Items out of scope -->
 <outscope>
   <li>project breakdown;</li>   
   <li>organizational structure.</li>
 </outscope>

 
