	<p>The entities defined within the work structure type extend lists are 
	obtained from the following modules:
	</p>
	
	<ul>
        <li><module_ref linkend="Observation:introduction">
          Observation_arm</module_ref>
        (ISO 10303-1258);</li>
	
        <li><module_ref linkend="Work_order:introduction">
          Work_order_type_arm</module_ref>
        (ISO 10303-1243);</li>
	
        <li><module_ref linkend="Work_output:introduction">
          Work_output_arm</module_ref>
        (ISO 10303-1300);</li>
	
        <li><module_ref linkend="Work_request:introduction">
          Work_request_arm</module_ref>
        (ISO 10303-1042).</li>
	
	</ul>
	
	 <p>From the perspective of information cross coupling; the type extend lists 
	 identified within this module specify how all work structure information modelling 
	 concepts defined within the schemas of the work structure domain are coupled together 
	 via type extends within the work structure domain.</p>
	 
